## SECTION A: Three Critical Architecture Changes (P0 — Non-Negotiable)

### A1. Replace Claude-Only Intelligence Layer with Multi-Model LLM Router (LiteLLM)

The Intelligence Layer must NOT be hardcoded to Claude. Redesign it with a **model-agnostic abstraction layer using LiteLLM** as the routing/proxy service.

**What LiteLLM provides:**
- Unified OpenAI-compatible API across 100+ providers (Anthropic, OpenRouter, Google, Mistral, etc.)
- Built-in fallback chains, retry logic, and load balancing
- Per-request cost tracking (critical for per-org billing)
- Streaming support
- Can be self-hosted as a lightweight proxy alongside the Agent Engine worker

**Update the Tech Stack table:**

| Component | Old | New |
|-----------|-----|-----|
| LLM Primary | Claude Sonnet via Anthropic API | **LiteLLM Router** → routes to appropriate model per task |
| LLM Fallback | OpenRouter (manual) | **Built into LiteLLM** (automatic fallback chains) |
| LLM Local | Ollama (out of scope) | Keep deferred — LiteLLM supports it when ready |
| Video Generation | `veo3-mcp` (Google Veo 3) | **`video-mcp`** wrapping **fal.ai** API |

**Add this model routing table to the Intelligence Layer section:**

| Agent / Task | Primary Model | Fallback Model | Rationale |
|-------------|---------------|----------------|-----------|
| PRESELL Agent (WhatsApp qualification) | Claude 3.5 Haiku (via Anthropic) | GPT-4o-mini (via OpenRouter) | Fast response needed, conversational quality, cost-effective |
| GUARDIAN Agent (invoice analysis) | Claude Sonnet (via Anthropic) | GPT-4o (via OpenRouter) | Highest reasoning quality needed for financial decisions |
| ADENGINE Agent (copy generation) | GPT-4o-mini (via OpenRouter) | Claude Haiku | Creative writing, cost-sensitive, high volume |
| MASTER Agent (morning brief) | GPT-4o-mini (via OpenRouter) | Claude Haiku | Summarisation is simpler, cost-sensitive |
| Lead scoring | Rule-based engine (NO LLM) | N/A | Deterministic — must NOT use an LLM |
| Photo analysis (GUARDIAN) | GPT-4o Vision (via OpenRouter) | Claude Vision | Multi-modal capability needed |
| Video generation | fal.ai | None | Replaces Veo3 — more accessible API, better pricing |
| Ad copy variants | GPT-4o-mini | Claude Haiku | High volume, cost-sensitive |

**Add this new table to the Data Models section:**

```sql
CREATE TABLE llm_config (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  organisation_id UUID REFERENCES organisations(id),
  task_type TEXT NOT NULL, -- 'presell', 'guardian', 'adengine', 'master', 'photo_analysis', 'video_gen'
  primary_provider TEXT NOT NULL, -- 'anthropic', 'openrouter', 'fal_ai'
  primary_model TEXT NOT NULL, -- e.g. 'claude-3-5-haiku-20241022', 'gpt-4o-mini'
  fallback_provider TEXT,
  fallback_model TEXT,
  max_tokens INTEGER DEFAULT 4096,
  temperature NUMERIC DEFAULT 0.7,
  monthly_budget_kobo INTEGER, -- per-org per-task cost cap
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),
  UNIQUE(organisation_id, task_type)
);
```

**Add these columns to `agent_logs`:**
- `model_used TEXT` — which model actually handled the request
- `input_tokens INTEGER`
- `output_tokens INTEGER`
- `cost_usd NUMERIC`
- `provider TEXT` — 'anthropic', 'openrouter', 'fal_ai', etc.

**Update the architecture diagram** to show LiteLLM between the Agent Engine and the model providers. The Agent Engine calls LiteLLM, LiteLLM routes to the appropriate provider.

**Update all references** from "Claude Sonnet (Anthropic API)" to "LiteLLM Router → [appropriate model per task]" throughout the document.

**Per-org LLM cost caps:**

